  author={Saavedra-Peña, Nelson E. and Darbali-Zamora, Rachid and Desarden-Carrero, Edgardo and Aponte-Bezares, Erick},
  booktitle={2021 IEEE 48th Photovoltaic Specialists Conference (PVSC)}, 
  title={Towards an Islanding Detection Method Using a Digital Twin Concept}, 
  year={2021},
  volume={},
  number={},
  pages={0410-0415},
  abstract={In this paper, the development of a mathematical model for islanding detection method based on the concept of a digital twin is presented. The model estimates the grid impedance seen by a distributed energy resource. The proposed algorithm has characteristics of passive and active islanding detection methods. Using a discrete state-space representation of a dq0 axis power system as equality constraints, a digital twin is optimized to match the power system of interest. The concept is to use the estimated grid impedance as the parameter to identify the difference between normal operation and islanding scenarios. Selecting arbitrary initial values, the digital twin approximates the response of the actual system and therefore a value for the system impedance. Results indicate that the proposed method has the potential to estimate the grid impedance at the point of common coupling.},
  keywords={},
