  title={A System of Remote Duty Expressway Toll Station based on Multi Queue Digital Twin and Edge Decision}, 
  year={2022},
  volume={},
  number={},
  pages={173-174},
  abstract={At present, the expressway toll stations use electronic toll collection (ETC) and manual toll collection (MTC) two kinds of toll collection system. ETC has improved the traffic efficiency to a certain extent, but for the abnormal situation, it still needs to be solved manually on the spot, and a considerable number of cars do not use ETC, which fails to solve the problems of overstaffing, high labor intensity, low work efficiency, high expressway operation cost and poor service quality. Based on Internet of things, multi queue digital twin, edge decision technologies, our system has built an expressway operation mode of remote duty, which has got rid of the excessive dependence on staff in scenes such as cars getting on and off the lane and abnormal treatment. Finally, realizes cost reduction and efficiency of highway operation through remote centralized control of multiple lanes and multiple toll stations.},
  keywords={},
